HARARE - The decision by President Robert Mugabe&rsquo;s stone-broke government to implement a five percent health levy on airtime and mobile data will hit hard long-suffering ordinary Zimbabweans who are reeling from multiple effects of a dying economy, experts say. This comes as two weeks ago, government enacted the new tax into law through the Finance Act of 2017, leaving mobile network operators with no choice but to comply and collect the tax on its behalf.